#X text 1186 791 - CONTINUOUS FREQUENCY [1(CYCLE)/SEC = HZ]. DISCRETE FREQUENCY [1(CYCLE)/SAMPLE] \; - SO IF DISCRETE FREQEUNCY == 128! \, MEANS THAT WITH EACH SAMPLE WE HAVE 1 ROTATION -> ALWAYS 1 \; - FREQUENCY BINS: [0: (WINDOW-SIZE)-1] --> DISCRETE FREQUENCY. WHY? \; - FUNDAMENTAL FREQUENCY: SR/(WINDOW-SIZE) [HZ]. WHY? BECASUE OF ANALYSIS WINDOW SIZE? \; - FOR BETTER UNDERSTANDING INPUT FREQUENCY (HZ) IS DEFINED AS INTEGER/NON-INTEGER MULTIPLES OF FUNDAMENTAL FREQUENCY FROM 0 TILL NYQUIST FREQUNCY N/2, f 102;
#X text 140 269 DISCRETE->CONTINUOUS FREQUENCY CONVERSION;
#X floatatom 21 206 10 0 0 1 INPUT\ SIGNAL\ DISCRETE\ FREQUNECY\ [CYCLE/SAMPLE] - - 0;
#X text 328 17 DSP;
#X text 606 924 TO SYNCH SNAP-SHOT WITH PHASE;
